When you do 

ps -ef | grep 'FOLDERNAME' 

It will show the workflows running in that folder with the corresponding 
process ids. Now you need to kill the process ids to kill the workflows. 

kill -9 'process id'
They will give the command as ps -eaf |grep pmdtm or functional id (name of which the informatica was installed) then it will show the list of sessions that are running. So now if you go to sesslog/wokflow log you will find the process id of the ses/wflw you can use that id for reference and check with the list in unix and then its matched you can kill it using the command 

kill -l  
1) SIGHUP       2) SIGINT       3) SIGQUIT      4) SIGILL
 5) SIGTRAP      6) SIGABRT      7) SIGBUS       8) SIGFPE
 9) SIGKILL     10) SIGUSR1 

kill -9 process id eg: kill -9 19412 

