Server Deployments on Ubuntu with Docker and Supervisor
--name sets our container's name.
-a stdout -a stderr gets the internal process' stream so we can use supervisor to log.
Stopping a container does not delete it. --rm removes the container once it's stopped.
-p 3000:3000 forwards our host's port 3000 to our container's port 3000.
You can set environment variables inside the container. ie. -e PORT=3000

docker run --name shopwiz.net -a stdout -a stderr --rm=true  -p 80:80 shopwiz/roni -v /home/ubuntu/deploy:/app -e PORT=3000 me/shopwiz.net python server.py

docker run --name myapp -a stdout -a stderr --rm=true -p 3000:3000 -v /home/ubuntu/deploy:/app -e PORT=3000 me/myapp python server.py
