If you do use eval, you really need to use double-quotes (eval "$i") to avoid extra-extra-weird effects. For example, try this with a="cat -nT index.php |grep ' .* '" (i.e. the regex should match two spaces with any sequence of characters between them) and see what actually happens. For extra credit, explain why it happens. ñ Gordon Davisson Nov 24 '13 at 20:59 



