#####################
SPDY has been supported in nginx since version 1.3.15. In order to be able to use SPDY, you will need to have a recent version of nginx and OpenSSL version 1.0.0d or newer.

You can find out what version of OpenSSL you have installed by running openssl version. The command for nginx is nginx -v.

Once you've made sure your system supports SPDY, you can enable it by adding spdy to the listen line in your server block:

server {
    listen 443 ssl spdy;
}

Finally, restart nginx so that the changed can take effect:

sudo nginx -t
sudo service nginx restart
