As requested, posting my comment as a proper answer:

You can default this to, for example, sites/all/modules/contrib, in your .drush/drushrc.php* file:

$command_specific['dl'] = array('destination' => 'sites/all/modules/contrib'); 

Also note, you won't be able to exclude the 'modules' part of the path, as Drupal uses this to scan for modules.

Assuming I have an install profile called "my_profile", and I have a file in sites/all/drush/drushrc.php with the following contents:

<?php
$options['destination'] = 'profiles/my_profile/modules/contrib'; 

If I do the following:

    cd /path/to/drupal-docroot
    drush dl views

Then views is downloaded to /path/to/drupal-docroot/profiles/my_profile/modules/contrib/views

