Get emails from Gmail inbox with PHP

Retrieve Your Gmail Emails Using PHP and IMAP

function loadGmailMails($from=0,$to=0){
$hostname = ë{imap.gmail.com:993/imap/ssl}INBOXí;
$username = ëdioli.luca@gmail.comí;
$password = î;

$inbox = imap_open($hostname,$username,$password) or die(ëCannot connect to Gmail: ë . imap_last_error());
$e = imap_search($inbox,íALLí);

$emails = array();

if($e) {
rsort($e);//put the newest emails on top

if($to == 0) $to = sizeof($e);

for($i=$from;$i<$to;$i++){
$overview = imap_fetch_overview($inbox,$e[$i],0);
$message = imap_fetchbody($inbox,$e[$i],2);

preg_match('/(?P[a-zA-Z ]+)<(?P
.+)>/í,$overview[0]->from,$match);
trim($match[ënameí]);

$emails[] = array(ëreadí => $overview[0]->seen, ësubjectí => $overview[0]->subject, ëfromí => array(ënameí => $match[ënameí], ëaddressí => $match[ëaddressí]), ëdateí => $overview[0]->date, ëmessageí => $message);
}
}

imap_close($inbox);

return $emails;
}

Installing PHPUnit Test on Ubuntu

Type following command on your terminal.
i) pear

ii) sudo pear channel-discover pear.phpunit.de

iii) sudo pear channel-discover components.ez.no

iv) sudo pear channel-discover pear.symfony-project.com

v) sudo pear install phpunit/PHPUnit

The above outlined the normal procedural steps necessary to get PHPUnit installed on your system.

To check your PHPUnit installation type:

vi) phpunit

If installation is successful, you will see:

PHPUnit 3.5.15 by Sebastian Bergmann.


 	Note: When you create a new database, you must only specify the first three arguments to the mysqli object (servername, username and password).

Tip: If you have to use a specific port, add an empty string for the database-name argument, like this: new mysqli("localhost", "username", "password", "", port)

