The difference Between Document.Ready() v/s Window.Load

$(document).ready(function() { is jQuery event that is fired when DOM is loaded, so itís fired when the document structure is ready.

$(document).ready(function() {
alert(ìdocument ready occurred!î);
});

$(window).load() event is fired after whole content is loaded.

$(window).load(function() {
alert(ìwindow load occurred!î);
});
