If this is any help to someone else, I ran into a similar issue after cloning my live site on my local dev environment. Taking ideas from here, I had it resolved by changing
 "max_allowed_packet = 1M" to "max_allowed_packet = 2M" in my.ini file.
*****************
/etc/init.d/mysql restart

/etc/init.d/mysql 

Afterwards, add this setting to my.cnf under the [mysqld] section:

[mysqld]
max_allowed_packet = 256M

error_page 404 /index.php

innodb_buffer_pool_size = 512M
 innodb_buffer_pool_instances = 1
 innodb_flush_method = O_DIRECT
+max_allowed_packet = 256M
 
 [mysqldump]
 max_allowed_packet = 32M



