 symlink.sh
#!/bin/bash
# Location: Anywhere
sudo ln -s /etc/nginx/sites-available/domain.tld.conf /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/domain.tld.conf;
sudo service nginx restart;
 @natanfelles
Owner
natanfelles commented on 7 May 2016 • edited
Change domain.tld by your domain.

Create the virtual host file like this: /etc/nginx/sites-available/domain.tld.conf.
Edit your hosts file in /etc/hosts.
Create the index file to test the configurations like: /var/www/domain.tld/public/index.php.
Create the symlink to enable the virtual host then restart nginx server.
If anything do not work. Execute nginx on the terminal (as root) to see the error output.



